Dia. 03 Wrong Direction
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par The conclusion is, White has to play the tiger's mouth move.
\par Therefore White 1 is a good try, but the direction is wrong.
\par
\par Black's \cf1\b placement\cf0\b0  at 2 is \cf1\b severe\cf0\b0 . After White 3, Black plays hane at 4 and White dies. It is painful for White that he can't cut with A.
